menu "TapTalk"

    config TAPTALK_ENABLE_HID
        bool "Enumerate as a USB HID keyboard"
        default y
        help
            Installs TinyUSB and types transcripts into the host.

            Turning this OFF is a bring-up aid: TinyUSB takes over the USB PHY
            from the USB-Serial-JTAG controller, so with it on you can no
            longer flash over USB while the app runs (hold BOOT, tap PWR), and
            the console moves to the composite CDC interface. With it off, the
            transcript is only logged.

    config TAPTALK_TRAILING_SPACE
        bool "Type a space after each transcript"
        default y
        help
            Lets you dictate several phrases in a row without them running
            together. Never types Enter: that would submit forms.

    config TAPTALK_KEY_INTERVAL_MS
        int "Milliseconds between keystrokes"
        default 6
        range 2 50
        help
            A USB boot keyboard is polled every few milliseconds. Sending
            faster than the host polls loses keys. Raise this if characters go
            missing on a particular machine.

    config TAPTALK_BEEP
        bool "Confirmation tones through the speaker"
        default y
        help
            The board has no haptic motor, so a short tone is the only way to
            confirm a press without looking at the screen.

            The press tone is played into the same room as the microphone that
            is about to start recording, so audio_capture.c discards the first
            BEEP_PRESS_MS of every clip. Turning this off also turns off that
            discard.

    config TAPTALK_HID_DELAY_MS
        int "Delay before installing TinyUSB (debug)"
        default 0
        range 0 60000
        help
            Installing TinyUSB moves the console from USB-Serial-JTAG to a CDC
            interface, and the USB-Serial-JTAG port disappears at that moment.
            Every log line before that is only visible on a port that then goes
            away -- which is why a boot-time hang looks like silence.

            Set this to e.g. 20000 to keep the boot console alive long enough to
            watch what happens. Leave it at 0 for real builds: it delays the
            keyboard becoming usable by exactly this much.

    config TAPTALK_WATCH_LVGL
        bool "Subscribe the LVGL task to the task watchdog (debug)"
        default n
        help
            Makes a wedged render task print its own backtrace every few
            seconds. Noisy on purpose; never enable in a real build.

endmenu
